   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Wonder: A &quot;first&quot; for kids in foster care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides a caring, consistent adult mentor to a child in foster care between the ages of 6-12. It will provide &quot;firsts&quot; and childhood experiences for the children in our program. 

Researchers have found that the single most important factor in building resiliency in children is the consistent presence of a caring, supportive person who provides unconditional love; nonjudgmental, active listening; and actions that communicate &quot;I am here for you.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
